<section class="section">
	<h2 class="section-title">
		卷首语
	</h2>
	{% if not is_2009 %}
	<p>亲爱的校友，</p>
	<p>
		密西根学院在2006年成立以来，为各行各业和知名学府的研究生院输送了大批具有国际意识和创新能力的领袖型工程人才。你们中有些已成长为所在行业的骨干，有些已经在科研领域取得累累硕果，有些在用所学的知识款款地回报社会，有些则选择继续深造以编织更加绚烂的未来。作为见证了你们走出密院、步入新的人生旅程的密院教师，我为你们所有人取得的成绩而感到无比骄傲。我同时相信，作为一名密院人，你们一定也为学院近年来取得的成就而荣耀。为了让我们的密院在现有成功的基础上走向更大的成功，我们希望能够吸收各方面的正能量。作为学院的重要组成部分，校友的建议和支持将成为学院未来发展的重要源动力。此次组织的问卷调查即是获得各位校友真情反馈的渠道之一，我谨代表全院教职员工和你们的学弟学妹向你们表示诚挚的谢意！
	</p>
	<p>
		最后，祝你们在今后的职业生涯中取得更大的辉煌。一次密院人，终生密院人！
	</p>

	<div style="width:10em; float:right;">
		郑 刚 <br>
		本科教学副院长 <br>
		交大密西根学院 <br>
	</div>

	{% else %}
	<p>Dear Graduating Seniors,</p>

	<p>
		The UM-SJTU Joint Institute was officially founded in 2006. Our goal is to prepare our students for a challenging and bright future career and for you to become truly global leaders in engineering or non-engineering professional fields. As the 4th graduating class of the JI, you are about to turn over the last page at JI and enter a whole new chapter of your lives. However, the page you are about to turn over will not be a closure with JI. After your graduation, you may choose to pursue academic advancement or start practicing in industrial sector; you might end up in different continents of the world speaking different languages. No matter where you are and what you are going to do, you will always carry the JI name with you. As an instructor who witnessed your professional and personal growth in these past four years, I am very proud of you and your achievements at JI, and am very appreciative of your contribution to the JI. At the same time, I believe as a JIer, you must be proud of the success that we have achieved together too. In order to gear JI towards a bigger success, we will always need your support. We value and rely very much on your feedback and suggestions that are regarded as one of the major driving forces for the continuous development and improvement of our institute. We take your feedback about the programs as the biggest gift your left for our institute. This senior exit survey you are about to participate in is a carefully designed channel to collect your valuable feedback. On behalf of the JI students, faculty, and staff, I thank you for your contribution in this effort.
	</p>

	<p>Finally, I wish you a glorious future career and a happy life. “Once a JIer, always a JIer”!</p>



	<p>
		Dr. Gang Zheng
		<br>
		Associate Dean for Undergraduate Education
	</p>
	{% endif %}
	<div class="clear:both"></div>
</section>
